<paragraph id="AD1C3696EF0ADE02FF07FB3DFEEB52B4" blockId="7.[189,798,1043,1922]" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis id="9FD7EA84EF0ADE02FF07FB3DFEBE53BD" bold="true" box="[189,367,1186,1210]" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Adult habitus.</emphasis>
General color pale yellow, white in alcohol. Head with slightly darker, but obscure markings over ocelli, lappets and posterolateral areas of occiput (
<figureCitation id="35982A13EF0ADE02FEF4FA92FE775222" box="[334,422,1293,1317]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[189,241,1575,1599]" captionTargetBox="[362,1287,215,1514]" captionTargetId="figure-49@6.[362,1269,215,1472]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 14-18. Anacroneuria kayceae male structures. 14. Head and pronotum. 15. Abdominal sternum 9. 16. Aedeagus, ventral. 17. Aedeagus, lateral. 18. Aedeagus, dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4760788" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4760788/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Pronotum pale along lateral margins and median suture, but with irregular, dark brown, sublateral bands. Ocelli narrowly separated; wings transparent, veins pale. Legs, antennae and palpi pale.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AD1C3696EF0ADE02FF07FA20FE14503D" blockId="7.[189,798,1043,1922]" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis id="9FD7EA84EF0ADE02FF07FA20FED352D0" bold="true" box="[189,258,1471,1495]" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Male.</emphasis>
Forewing length 
<quantity id="6A5B9B73EF0ADE02FE53FA20FD9552D1" box="[489,580,1471,1495]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="7" pageNumber="85" unit="mm" value="17.0">17 mm</quantity>
. Hammer almost cylindrical, but slightly wider at base than apex (
<figureCitation id="35982A13EF0ADE02FD4AFA7DFF0B5119" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[189,241,1575,1599]" captionTargetBox="[362,1287,215,1514]" captionTargetId="figure-49@6.[362,1269,215,1472]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 14-18. Anacroneuria kayceae male structures. 14. Head and pronotum. 15. Abdominal sternum 9. 16. Aedeagus, ventral. 17. Aedeagus, lateral. 18. Aedeagus, dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4760788" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4760788/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal apex truncate, lateral margins slightly expanded and appearing swollen at base (
<figureCitation id="35982A13EF0ADE02FD00F9B6FF0B5162" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[189,241,1575,1599]" captionTargetBox="[362,1287,215,1514]" captionTargetId="figure-49@6.[362,1269,215,1472]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 14-18. Anacroneuria kayceae male structures. 14. Head and pronotum. 15. Abdominal sternum 9. 16. Aedeagus, ventral. 17. Aedeagus, lateral. 18. Aedeagus, dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4760788" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4760788/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Figs. 16, 18</figureCitation>
); hooks strongly sclerotized at base with a distinct dark line outlining inner basal margin, and bearing a strong ventral keel from near midlength to near tips. Dorsal keel consists of two close-set, low ridges, extending for about half of apical area length (
<figureCitation id="35982A13EF0ADE02FD4AF944FF0B5010" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[189,241,1575,1599]" captionTargetBox="[362,1287,215,1514]" captionTargetId="figure-49@6.[362,1269,215,1472]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 14-18. Anacroneuria kayceae male structures. 14. Head and pronotum. 15. Abdominal sternum 9. 16. Aedeagus, ventral. 17. Aedeagus, lateral. 18. Aedeagus, dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4760788" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4760788/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). In lateral aspect much of aedeagal apex membranous (
<figureCitation id="35982A13EF0ADE02FEDDF8BDFE69503D" box="[359,440,1826,1850]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[189,241,1575,1599]" captionTargetBox="[362,1287,215,1514]" captionTargetId="figure-49@6.[362,1269,215,1472]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 14-18. Anacroneuria kayceae male structures. 14. Head and pronotum. 15. Abdominal sternum 9. 16. Aedeagus, ventral. 17. Aedeagus, lateral. 18. Aedeagus, dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4760788" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4760788/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AD1C3696EF0ADE02FF07F8D9FE715059" blockId="7.[189,798,1043,1922]" box="[189,416,1862,1886]" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">
