<subSubSection id="E5B9651DEF0ADE02FCF9FF7EFB605663" pageId="7" pageNumber="85" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="AD1C3696EF0ADE02FCF9FF7EFB605663" blockId="7.[835,1443,225,854]" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis id="9FD7EA84EF0ADE02FCF9FF7EFC1C57FE" bold="true" box="[835,973,225,249]" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Etymology.</emphasis>
We honor Dr. Kayce Anderson, Colorado State University, for her dedication to ecological studies in 
<collectingCountry id="D5B47606EF0ADE02FB81FEB7FB715647" box="[1083,1184,296,320]" name="Ecuador" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, and her appreciation of Neotropical aquatic biology.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E5B9651DEF0ADE02FCF9FEF0FBDC5409" pageId="7" pageNumber="85" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="AD1C3696EF0ADE02FCF9FEF0FBDC5409" blockId="7.[835,1443,225,854]" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis id="9FD7EA84EF0ADE02FCF9FEF0FC155680" bold="true" box="[835,964,367,391]" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The aedeagus of this species is similar to that of the Peruvian-Bolivian species, 
<taxonomicName id="6AA34D15EF0ADE02FAADFE0CFBE156C8" authority="Stark &amp; Sivec 1998" authorityName="Stark &amp; Sivec" authorityYear="1998" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachacuti">
<emphasis id="9FD7EA84EF0ADE02FAADFE0CFA7256AC" box="[1303,1443,403,427]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">A. pachacuti</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="C9324B67EF0ADE02FCF9FE29FBE156C8" author="Stark, B. P. &amp; I. Sivec" box="[835,1072,438,463]" pageId="7" pageNumber="85" pagination="1 - 64" refId="ref6613" refString="Stark, B. P. &amp; I. Sivec. 1998. Anacroneuria of Peru and Bolivia (Plecoptera: Perlidae). Scopolia, 40: 1 - 64." type="journal article" year="1998">Stark &amp; Sivec 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, particularly in lateral aspect. However, in that species the apical section of the aedeagus is offset by prominent basolateral notches and the aedeagal apex is nipple-shaped rather than truncate (see 
<bibRefCitation id="C9324B67EF0ADE02FC5FFDDAFB18555A" author="Stark, B. P. &amp; I. Sivec" box="[997,1225,581,605]" pageId="7" pageNumber="85" pagination="1 - 64" refId="ref6613" refString="Stark, B. P. &amp; I. Sivec. 1998. Anacroneuria of Peru and Bolivia (Plecoptera: Perlidae). Scopolia, 40: 1 - 64." type="journal article" year="1998">Stark &amp; Sivec 1998</bibRefCitation>
, Figs. 124-126). In addition, 
<taxonomicName id="6AA34D15EF0ADE02FC0CFDF7FBEF5587" authorityName="Stark &amp; Sivec" authorityYear="1998" box="[950,1086,616,640]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachacuti">
<emphasis id="9FD7EA84EF0ADE02FC0CFDF7FBEF5587" box="[950,1086,616,640]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">A. pachacuti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a smaller species (FWL ~ 
<quantity id="6A5B9B73EF0ADE02FA33FDF7FCA255A3" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="7" pageNumber="85" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
) with a slightly darker habitus. The aedeagus is also similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="6AA34D15EF0ADE02FBF0FD2FFA8155C0" authority="Stark, 2001" authorityName="Stark" authorityYear="2001" box="[1098,1360,687,711]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rawlinsi">
<emphasis id="9FD7EA84EF0ADE02FBF0FD2FFB1555C0" box="[1098,1220,687,711]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">A. rawlinsi</emphasis>
Stark, 2001
</taxonomicName>
, but in that species the apical aedeagal section lacks swollen basolateral lobes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E5B9651DEF0ADE02FCF9FC85FB785451" pageId="7" pageNumber="85" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="AD1C3696EF0ADE02FCF9FC85FB785451" blockId="7.[835,1443,225,854]" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis id="9FD7EA84EF0ADE02FCF9FC85FC1C5435" bold="true" box="[835,973,794,818]" pageId="7" pageNumber="85">Comments.</emphasis>
The 
